Step 2: Organise and Describe the Data

There are five input signals and one output signal:

    IGN (Ignition): Active-HIGH (1 = On, 0 = Off).

    DRIV (Driver Presence): Active-HIGH (1 = Occupied, 0 = Empty).

    PASS (Passenger Presence): Active-HIGH (1 = Occupied, 0 = Empty).

    BELTD (Driver Seatbelt): Active-LOW (0 = Unfastened, 1 = Fastened).

    BELTP (Passenger Seatbelt): Active-LOW (0 = Unfastened, 1 = Fastened).

    ALARM (Output): Active-LOW (0 = Sounding, 1 = Silent).
